WEBVTT

00:20.020 --> 00:22.148
[Pat]
Previously on Shining Vale...

00:22.314 --> 00:23.357
[Robyn] This is Pat Phelps.

00:23.482 --> 00:25.443
She bought the big house
on Elm.

00:25.609 --> 00:27.903
[Terry]
Welcome to Casa de Phelps.

00:28.028 --> 00:30.114
[Gaynor] In other words,
Mom boned some rando,

00:30.281 --> 00:31.782
-so we had to move here.
-Hey, no!

00:31.949 --> 00:33.617
I've been in a really
dark place lately.

00:33.784 --> 00:35.911
I have to finish
this fucking book.

00:36.036 --> 00:37.371
Kam says if I don't write it,

00:37.538 --> 00:38.956
I have to give
the advance back.

00:39.081 --> 00:41.625
-You can do anything.
-[all] We are Phelps!

00:41.792 --> 00:43.502
[Pat] There's something
very wrong with this house.

00:43.669 --> 00:44.879
[Jake] Now is the game over?

00:45.045 --> 00:46.422
[Daisy] Not until you're dead.

00:46.589 --> 00:47.590
You think I'm going crazy?

00:47.715 --> 00:48.883
I'm just really fucking sad.

00:49.049 --> 00:50.718
Just take the clonazepam.

00:50.885 --> 00:53.637
[Pat] My mother was my age
when she went psychotic.

00:53.804 --> 00:55.890
You're worried
you're gonna turn out like her.

00:56.056 --> 00:58.142
-[Terry] Pat's seeing ghosts.
-[Pat] It's a '50s housewife.

00:58.267 --> 01:00.144
-I'm Rosemary.
-[Pat] She's like my muse.

01:00.311 --> 01:02.146
So now I just take
a little vitamin C,

01:02.313 --> 01:03.898
and she practically writes it
for me.

01:04.063 --> 01:05.357
I need your help
to finish my book.

01:05.524 --> 01:06.984
Let me show you how it ends.

01:07.151 --> 01:09.653
[distorted voice]
We have a lot of work to do.

01:09.820 --> 01:13.032
[Terry] She chops up
her family with an axe.

01:13.199 --> 01:15.075
You set an impossible standard

01:15.201 --> 01:17.036
for what it means
to be a spouse!

01:17.203 --> 01:18.579
Because I wanted you
to be happy!

01:18.746 --> 01:20.414
I can't be happy!

01:23.667 --> 01:25.461
-[Pat] Oh, my God.
-Mom!

01:25.628 --> 01:27.505
[sighs]

01:27.670 --> 01:29.340
[doctor] You're in the Shining
Vale Psychiatric Hospital.

01:29.507 --> 01:31.175
[nurse] You overdosed
on expired barbiturates.

01:31.342 --> 01:32.926
-[Pat] I'm not crazy!
-It's okay, Mom.

01:33.051 --> 01:34.386
They're just gonna take care
of you for a little while.

01:34.553 --> 01:36.847
[Pat] I'm possessed!

01:37.014 --> 01:38.765
Are we gonna be okay?

01:38.933 --> 01:40.893
Yeah, we are Phelps.

01:42.186 --> 01:45.021
[dramatic music plays]

01:45.146 --> 01:48.150
♪ ♪

02:00.913 --> 02:03.499
[singer] ♪ La, la, la, la ♪

02:03.666 --> 02:06.669
♪ La, la, la, la, la ♪♪♪

02:06.794 --> 02:09.128
♪ La, la, la, la ♪

02:09.255 --> 02:12.341
♪ La, la, la, la, la ♪

02:12.508 --> 02:14.760
♪ La, la, la, la ♪♪♪

02:14.927 --> 02:17.429
♪ La, la, la, la, la ♪♪♪

02:17.596 --> 02:18.722
♪ La, la ♪♪♪

02:18.889 --> 02:20.307
Roxy, don't shit where you eat.

02:20.474 --> 02:21.475
[dog groans]

02:23.394 --> 02:25.728
[singer] ♪ La, la, la, la ♪

02:25.896 --> 02:28.816
♪ La, la, la, la ♪

02:28.983 --> 02:30.067
♪ La, la ♪♪♪

02:30.234 --> 02:31.735
[Gaynor] Jake, let's go!

02:31.902 --> 02:35.406
[singer] ♪ La, la, la, la, la ♪

02:35.573 --> 02:36.906
Coming.

02:37.074 --> 02:39.577
[singer]
♪ Your life was upended ♪♪♪

02:39.743 --> 02:43.079
♪ When darkness descended ♪

02:43.247 --> 02:47.710
♪ And these
Are just merely the facts ♪♪♪

02:47.877 --> 02:51.255
♪ The sudden upheaval ♪

02:51.422 --> 02:54.133
♪ When she went medieval ♪

02:54.300 --> 02:57.595
♪ And Mom hits your dad
With an axe ♪♪♪

02:57.761 --> 02:59.263
[door buzzes, closes]

02:59.430 --> 03:01.682
♪ La, la, la, la ♪♪♪

03:01.849 --> 03:04.977
♪ La, la, la, la, la ♪♪♪

03:05.144 --> 03:07.354
♪ La, la, la, la ♪

03:07.521 --> 03:10.357
♪ La, la, la, la, la ♪♪♪

03:10.524 --> 03:12.234
♪ La, la, la, la ♪♪♪

03:12.401 --> 03:13.611
[Jake] Gaynor!

03:13.777 --> 03:15.821
-[tires squealing]
-You forgot something!

03:15.988 --> 03:18.365
[singer] ♪ La, la ♪

03:19.909 --> 03:21.410
Father.

03:21.535 --> 03:24.413
[singer] ♪ There's no sense
In running... ♪

03:24.579 --> 03:25.581
Daughter.

03:25.748 --> 03:26.749
[singer] ♪ It's coming ♪

03:26.874 --> 03:27.875
♪ Anxiety... ♪

03:28.042 --> 03:29.293
[squeals in fear]

03:29.460 --> 03:31.962
[singer]
♪ ...plans her attacks ♪♪♪

03:32.129 --> 03:34.673
♪ So sit back and take it ♪♪♪

03:34.840 --> 03:37.968
♪ And somehow you'll make it ♪

03:38.135 --> 03:40.346
♪ When Mom hits your dad ♪♪♪

03:40.512 --> 03:43.766
♪ With an axe ♪♪♪

03:43.933 --> 03:46.852
♪ ♪

03:49.939 --> 03:51.357
[song ends]

03:51.523 --> 03:53.692
-Thank you, Shining Vale.
-[feedback whines]

03:55.069 --> 03:56.904
Somebody put gum in here.

03:57.071 --> 03:58.447
♪ ♪

03:58.572 --> 04:00.407
[door buzzes, closes]

04:00.574 --> 04:03.577
[Dr. Siferr] Try to relax, Pat.
We'll be done in no time.

04:03.744 --> 04:04.828
Mm.

04:04.954 --> 04:06.413
[Rosemary]
Just bite down on this.

04:06.580 --> 04:07.665
[Pat, muffled] No!

04:07.831 --> 04:09.708
[screaming]

04:09.875 --> 04:11.794
[device whirring]

04:11.961 --> 04:14.713
[Rosemary]
Hold on tight, Patricia.

04:14.880 --> 04:16.757
-[groans]
-[electricity crackling]

04:16.923 --> 04:18.341
[screams]

04:18.509 --> 04:21.261
[eerie music plays]

04:21.428 --> 04:24.431
♪ ♪♪♪

04:35.484 --> 04:38.362
[Gaynor]
Welcome home, Casa de Phelps.

04:40.739 --> 04:43.283
[Terry] It's so dirty.

04:43.409 --> 04:44.368
What happened?

04:44.534 --> 04:45.869
Well, our cleaning lady's been

04:45.995 --> 04:48.497
in an insane asylum
for four months, so...

04:48.664 --> 04:50.916
Oh, what the fuck?

04:51.041 --> 04:52.960
-[Terry] Fuck is that?
-[Gaynor] Hi.

04:53.127 --> 04:55.587
That's Roxy. You love her.

04:55.754 --> 04:58.799
-Why?
-Because it's Roxy.

04:58.966 --> 04:59.967
[Jake] Hi, Dad.

05:03.262 --> 05:04.430
Son.

05:05.889 --> 05:07.307
Dad.

05:07.433 --> 05:08.392
Son.

05:08.559 --> 05:09.727
Hmm.

05:09.893 --> 05:12.229
-Dad.
-[cries]

05:14.606 --> 05:16.900
[sniffles] Son.

05:20.738 --> 05:22.448
-Dad.
-Okay. Holy fuck, Jake.

05:22.614 --> 05:24.283
Please go do your homework.

05:24.450 --> 05:27.578
All right, Dad,
I'm gonna take you upstairs.

05:27.745 --> 05:30.456
[chuckles]

05:30.622 --> 05:32.416
[eerie music plays]

05:32.582 --> 05:33.417
[Gaynor, distant] Dad?

05:33.584 --> 05:36.545
♪ ♪♪♪

05:38.714 --> 05:39.798
[blade scrapes]

05:39.965 --> 05:42.426
I-I don't think
I'm going up there.

05:42.593 --> 05:45.387
[tweeting]

05:50.558 --> 05:53.604
[person screaming]

05:55.689 --> 05:57.066
Crazy day.

06:00.235 --> 06:02.196
Be better, Louise.

06:04.990 --> 06:07.284
Oh, no, thank you.
I don't smoke...

06:07.451 --> 06:10.871
or drink or curse
or do drugs anymore.

06:11.038 --> 06:14.166
I'm rehabilitated.
I've learned my lesson.

06:14.333 --> 06:17.086
I am no longer
a danger to society.

06:17.211 --> 06:18.921
That's the God's honest truth.

06:19.046 --> 06:21.423
What'd you have
for breakfast today?

06:21.590 --> 06:22.966
Um...

06:23.133 --> 06:24.885
I want to s-say oatmeal.

06:25.052 --> 06:27.137
You had grapefruit.

06:27.304 --> 06:28.847
You can't keep me locked up

06:29.014 --> 06:31.225
because I can't remember
what I had for breakfast.

06:31.391 --> 06:33.727
You may as well lock up
every woman over 40.

06:33.852 --> 06:35.354
What did you have
for breakfast?

06:35.479 --> 06:37.564
Black coffee, two Sweet'N Lows,
and a cigarette.

06:37.731 --> 06:38.982
You don't remember breakfast

06:39.149 --> 06:41.318
because
the electric-shock treatment

06:41.485 --> 06:43.153
wipes your short-term memory.

06:43.320 --> 06:46.824
And you have had... [whistles]

06:46.990 --> 06:49.409
...sixty-six treatments.

06:49.576 --> 06:51.954
And you zapped Rosemary
right out of me.

06:52.121 --> 06:54.248
I know she was a part
of my schizophrenia.

06:54.414 --> 06:57.334
Please, come on. Let me go.

06:57.501 --> 06:59.962
I mean, I've been here for...
[whistles]

07:00.129 --> 07:02.381
...four months.

07:02.548 --> 07:04.007
I've been doing this
a long time.

07:04.133 --> 07:05.425
I see what has happened

07:05.551 --> 07:07.177
to women who are released
too soon.

07:07.344 --> 07:10.013
They become dangerous,
immoral, whiney.

07:10.180 --> 07:11.640
I am better.

07:11.765 --> 07:14.226
I'm a wife and a mother,
and I need to go home.

07:14.393 --> 07:17.688
You are a psychotic wife
and mother.

07:17.855 --> 07:20.232
Ideally, you'd be here
for another three years.

07:20.357 --> 07:23.110
"Three years"?
My dog will be dead.

07:23.277 --> 07:24.403
I said "ideally."

07:24.570 --> 07:27.030
Unfortunately,
I can only keep you here

07:27.197 --> 07:29.741
until your insurance runs out.

07:29.908 --> 07:31.368
[door buzzes, closes]

07:31.535 --> 07:33.620
Hi. Pat Phelps.
I'm checking out.

07:33.787 --> 07:36.623
How'd they let you out
after only four months?

07:36.790 --> 07:38.542
I was locked away
for four years,

07:38.709 --> 07:40.127
and I just tried
to kill myself.

07:40.294 --> 07:43.422
I guess you have
better insurance than I do.

07:43.589 --> 07:45.883
Thanks for picking me up, Mom.

07:46.049 --> 07:48.427
That's what mothers do,

07:48.594 --> 07:50.637
and someday you'll do the same
for Gaynor.

07:50.804 --> 07:53.182
Oh, my gosh, I hope not.

07:54.433 --> 07:56.435
My poor kids. How are they?

07:57.811 --> 07:59.146
How should I know?

07:59.313 --> 08:00.856
You were supposed
to be taking care of them.

08:01.023 --> 08:02.357
Then I'm sure they're fine.

08:02.482 --> 08:03.942
Here are the clothes
you came in with.

08:04.109 --> 08:05.819
We couldn't get your husband's
blood out of your shirt.

08:05.944 --> 08:06.778
That's okay.

08:06.945 --> 08:08.363
And a prescription for lithium.

08:08.530 --> 08:10.699
Dr. Siferr wants to stick
with 600 milligrams.

08:10.866 --> 08:13.619
Six hundred?
That's a pediatric dose.

08:13.785 --> 08:14.953
I'm on 900.

08:15.120 --> 08:16.580
You win again, Mom.

08:16.747 --> 08:19.041
-[person screams] Help me!
-[electricity crackling]

08:19.207 --> 08:20.876
Please help me!

08:21.043 --> 08:23.462
No! Please help--

08:23.629 --> 08:25.005
Can I see your wrist, please?

08:25.172 --> 08:26.757
Oh, no, I-I tried with pills.

08:26.924 --> 08:28.967
She wants to cut off
your wristband.

08:29.134 --> 08:31.345
This is my daughter's
first time.

08:31.511 --> 08:32.511
[Pat] Sorry.

08:35.015 --> 08:37.808
Okay, Mrs. Phelps,
you're free to go.

08:37.976 --> 08:39.937
Thank you.

08:40.062 --> 08:42.438
I'm gonna go see my family.

08:42.606 --> 08:45.317
[door creaking]

08:45.484 --> 08:48.445
[insects chirping]

08:54.451 --> 08:55.994
Jake?

08:58.163 --> 09:00.290
Gaynor?

09:00.457 --> 09:02.125
Mommy's home.

09:02.292 --> 09:05.254
[house groaning]

09:09.508 --> 09:13.595
I am in control.

09:13.762 --> 09:16.932
-I am in--
-[dog barks]

09:17.057 --> 09:19.017
Oh. Roxy.

09:19.184 --> 09:20.894
Oh, baby.

09:21.061 --> 09:23.689
Oh, my goodness. Oh.

09:23.855 --> 09:27.025
Mm, Mommy's back.

09:27.192 --> 09:28.568
-[sighs] Oh.
-[door clicks]

09:28.735 --> 09:29.695
-[door creaks open]
-[chuckles]

09:29.861 --> 09:31.321
We both need a bath.

09:31.488 --> 09:34.324
[eerie music plays]

09:34.491 --> 09:37.494
♪ ♪♪♪

09:46.795 --> 09:49.256
[eerie thud]

09:49.423 --> 09:51.174
I am in control.

09:51.341 --> 09:54.303
♪ ♪♪♪

10:07.607 --> 10:09.192
Oh, fudge me!

10:09.359 --> 10:10.694
Mom.

10:10.819 --> 10:13.071
-Jake?
-Mom.

10:17.326 --> 10:18.869
[Pat] Oh.

10:19.036 --> 10:21.204
Oh, my baby.

10:21.371 --> 10:22.497
Oh.

10:22.664 --> 10:24.124
You must have
so many questions.

10:24.291 --> 10:25.834
Do we have pizza pockets?

10:26.001 --> 10:27.085
What?

10:27.252 --> 10:29.546
Pizza pockets.
My friends are hungry.

10:29.713 --> 10:32.049
Friends, plural?

10:32.215 --> 10:34.468
Yes. I'm popular now.

10:35.927 --> 10:38.388
Are these adults?
Did you meet them online?

10:38.555 --> 10:40.766
I met them at sports.
I'm a mascot now.

10:40.932 --> 10:42.392
Bro, this is lame.

10:42.559 --> 10:43.935
Let's go play Five Nights
on the VR.

10:44.102 --> 10:46.980
No. I don't play VR anymore.
It's for virgins.

10:47.147 --> 10:48.815
What happened while I was gone?

10:48.982 --> 10:50.484
Dude, you still scared
of that girl?

10:50.650 --> 10:52.819
No, I'm just not a nerd, okay?

10:52.986 --> 10:54.654
So let's just go use my drone

10:54.821 --> 10:56.948
to go check the accuracy
of Google Maps.

10:58.617 --> 10:59.618
Bye.

10:59.785 --> 11:01.536
I missed you.

11:07.542 --> 11:08.794
Oh.

11:08.960 --> 11:11.838
[soft music plays]

11:11.963 --> 11:13.632
♪ ♪

11:13.799 --> 11:15.550
Oh.

11:15.717 --> 11:17.677
That felt good.

11:17.844 --> 11:20.722
♪ ♪

11:20.847 --> 11:23.892
Oh, your friends went that way.

11:24.017 --> 11:25.852
[creepy music plays]

11:26.019 --> 11:28.313
[goat bleats]

11:28.438 --> 11:31.400
♪ ♪♪♪

11:39.408 --> 11:41.159
[goat bleats]

11:45.497 --> 11:46.623
[Pat] Gaynor.

11:49.418 --> 11:50.627
Mom.

11:57.676 --> 11:59.845
[soft music plays]

12:00.011 --> 12:01.513
[Pat] Oh.

12:02.722 --> 12:04.474
[sighs] I know.

12:04.599 --> 12:08.645
I know. I know.
[exhales deeply]

12:08.812 --> 12:09.980
I forgive you.

12:11.481 --> 12:13.733
Excuse me?

12:13.900 --> 12:15.819
Forgive me for what?

12:15.986 --> 12:19.197
For having me committed.

12:19.364 --> 12:20.657
I know that's not easy.

12:20.824 --> 12:22.075
Well, you made it easier

12:22.242 --> 12:24.202
by trying to chop up
your family with an axe.

12:24.369 --> 12:27.247
Okay, to be fair, I never tried
to chop up Jake or Roxy.

12:27.414 --> 12:29.332
How about saying
you're fucking sorry?

12:29.458 --> 12:30.876
You're right. Let's go back.

12:31.042 --> 12:32.669
-I'm sorry.
-Hmm.

12:32.794 --> 12:35.839
[Pat] Hey, how are you?

12:36.006 --> 12:37.382
How do you think I am?

12:37.507 --> 12:39.342
I had to take care
of your mess for four months.

12:39.509 --> 12:42.387
I feel like I went back,
and you didn't go back.

12:42.554 --> 12:44.389
Okay, whatever, Mom.

12:44.556 --> 12:46.808
And why are you home?

12:47.893 --> 12:50.187
Because I'm better.

12:50.353 --> 12:52.272
And I'm gonna take care
of this family.

12:52.439 --> 12:53.732
Well, Jake and I
don't need you,

12:53.899 --> 12:55.442
and Dad doesn't remember you.

12:55.609 --> 12:56.776
-What?
-[Gaynor] Don't worry.

12:56.943 --> 12:58.361
I didn't tell him
what happened,

12:58.528 --> 13:00.280
and he didn't hear my song
about it, so...

13:00.405 --> 13:01.573
Thank you.

13:01.698 --> 13:04.201
I didn't do it for you.
I did it for Dad.

13:04.367 --> 13:06.995
His doctor said
it would be too traumatic.

13:07.162 --> 13:08.872
He's afraid of Roxy,
and he calls me Button.

13:09.039 --> 13:11.291
Button? Good gravy.

13:11.458 --> 13:13.793
Did you just say "good gravy"?

13:13.919 --> 13:16.254
I don't curse anymore.

13:16.421 --> 13:18.507
Yeah, they zapped it out of me.

13:18.673 --> 13:20.091
Oh, wow.

13:20.217 --> 13:23.178
Well, I guess there goes
your whole fucking personality.

13:27.974 --> 13:30.477
I missed you.

13:30.644 --> 13:33.522
[dissonant piano notes playing]

13:33.688 --> 13:35.148
♪ ♪

13:35.315 --> 13:37.901
[sighs] I'm in control.

13:38.068 --> 13:41.029
♪ ♪

13:57.879 --> 13:59.130
Terry?

14:01.216 --> 14:02.008
Patty?

14:02.175 --> 14:04.052
Yeah.

14:04.219 --> 14:06.304
-It's Pat.
-[Terry] Wow.

14:06.471 --> 14:10.141
You're even more beautiful
than in your pictures.

14:10.308 --> 14:12.894
And you have a beard.

14:15.605 --> 14:17.649
[dissonant piano notes playing]

14:17.816 --> 14:20.193
Sorry.
I don't know what happened.

14:20.360 --> 14:21.945
I'm... [chuckles]

14:22.070 --> 14:24.364
-Sorry.
-That's okay.

14:27.033 --> 14:28.785
Oh, Terry.

14:30.829 --> 14:33.415
-[cries softly, sniffles]
-Why are you crying?

14:33.540 --> 14:36.835
I'm just so happy to see you.

14:37.002 --> 14:38.837
Um...

14:39.004 --> 14:41.298
is it true that you
don't remember anything?

14:41.464 --> 14:43.592
No. I...

14:43.758 --> 14:45.218
I remember things.

14:45.385 --> 14:46.845
Uh-oh. [chuckles]

14:46.970 --> 14:47.846
Like what?

14:48.013 --> 14:50.098
I remember you're...

14:50.265 --> 14:51.641
a writer

14:51.808 --> 14:53.518
and that you're funny

14:53.685 --> 14:55.812
and that when I...

14:55.979 --> 14:57.981
slipped and fell
down the stairs,

14:58.148 --> 15:00.483
you got sad, so you went
to the hospital.

15:00.609 --> 15:02.694
Yep, those are
the bullet points.

15:02.861 --> 15:05.655
And--and the phone
is helping me

15:05.822 --> 15:07.699
with my memory, and...

15:08.867 --> 15:11.870
And here's you.

15:12.037 --> 15:14.998
And... and that's Jake.

15:15.165 --> 15:17.417
He is my son.

15:19.044 --> 15:21.504
And that's Button.

15:21.671 --> 15:24.883
That's...the dog.

15:26.217 --> 15:28.928
And this man's very happy.
I mean, he's--

15:29.095 --> 15:30.263
-I don't know who he is.
-Yeah, that's, um--

15:30.430 --> 15:31.723
that's your cousin Albert.

15:31.890 --> 15:33.683
Um, he is dead.

15:33.850 --> 15:37.354
-So let's erase that, okay?
-Pat?

15:37.520 --> 15:38.938
Was I a good husband?

15:39.105 --> 15:43.109
Oh, Terry,
you were the best husband.

15:43.276 --> 15:45.445
Were you a good wife?

15:45.570 --> 15:47.572
I was okay.

15:47.739 --> 15:49.366
I'm gonna be better.

15:49.532 --> 15:52.118
I'm gonna be
the best wife and mother.

15:52.243 --> 15:53.620
I promise.

15:53.745 --> 15:55.955
I'm gonna start
by cleaning this place up,

15:56.122 --> 15:58.333
and I'm gonna make
a big family dinner.

15:58.500 --> 15:59.709
You need to rest.

15:59.876 --> 16:02.462
No, I've got way too much
to catch up on.

16:02.629 --> 16:05.465
You need to take care
of yourself.

16:07.175 --> 16:10.095
Okay.
Maybe just for one minute.

16:10.261 --> 16:13.139
[eerie music plays]

16:14.683 --> 16:16.601
[drone buzzing]

16:16.768 --> 16:18.770
[Jake] Come back!
I command you!

16:18.937 --> 16:21.189
[buzzing continues]

16:24.109 --> 16:26.945
[static whirring]

16:27.112 --> 16:29.948
[ominous music plays]

16:30.115 --> 16:31.658
♪ ♪♪♪

16:31.825 --> 16:33.368
What?

16:33.535 --> 16:35.495
[Daisy] Jake.

16:35.620 --> 16:38.415
♪ ♪♪♪

16:40.875 --> 16:42.502
[whispering] Jake.

16:43.878 --> 16:45.588
-I'm up!
-Why?

16:45.755 --> 16:48.508
[drone buzzing]

16:49.968 --> 16:52.595
[Terry] "Patty, it was nice
to see you.

16:52.762 --> 16:55.265
"Going out with Button.
Be back later.

16:55.390 --> 16:57.434
Love, Terry."

16:57.600 --> 16:58.560
What the heck?

16:58.727 --> 17:01.521
[electronic music playing]

17:01.688 --> 17:04.482
Dad, Jake, come on. Let's go.

17:04.648 --> 17:06.818
I'm sorry I overslept.

17:06.984 --> 17:10.029
Um, why don't you just give me
a minute to brush everything?

17:10.155 --> 17:11.489
And I'll take you to school.

17:11.656 --> 17:13.324
No, that's okay. I got it.

17:13.450 --> 17:15.242
No, really, it--
I don't--I don't mind.

17:15.410 --> 17:17.704
Mom, I dropped
out of school, so...

17:17.871 --> 17:19.955
Jeepers.

17:20.123 --> 17:21.708
You have to go back.

17:21.833 --> 17:23.292
Well, gosh, gee whiz, Mom.

17:23.460 --> 17:25.502
How do I know you're not
gonna go batshit again?

17:25.627 --> 17:29.257
Because I am in control.

17:29.382 --> 17:31.634
That's not helping me.

17:31.801 --> 17:33.178
[Terry] Hey.

17:33.344 --> 17:34.179
Oh.

17:34.345 --> 17:35.972
Pat! Damn it.

17:37.056 --> 17:38.099
Patty.

17:38.266 --> 17:40.685
[door clattering]

17:40.852 --> 17:41.978
Pat.

17:45.899 --> 17:48.526
Honey, can I help you?

17:48.693 --> 17:49.986
I got it.

17:52.781 --> 17:54.574
[exhales sharply]

17:54.741 --> 17:56.034
I got it.

17:56.201 --> 17:58.995
[dramatic rock music plays]

17:59.162 --> 18:01.998
♪ ♪

18:02.165 --> 18:03.917
-Sure I can't help?
-He says he's got it.

18:04.042 --> 18:07.003
♪ ♪

18:09.547 --> 18:11.382
[Terry] Ah.

18:11.549 --> 18:14.344
♪ ♪♪♪

18:14.469 --> 18:18.556
This happened yesterday.
It gets stuck on this track.

18:18.723 --> 18:20.183
You know what, honey?
Just go without me.

18:20.350 --> 18:23.186
No, you got this, Dad.

18:23.353 --> 18:25.021
-Oh, for fig's sake, Terry.
-No, don't touch him.

18:25.188 --> 18:27.273
I got it. There we go.

18:27.440 --> 18:29.359
I got it.

18:29.526 --> 18:30.819
Got to run.

18:30.985 --> 18:33.780
♪ ♪

18:33.947 --> 18:36.908
[drone buzzing]

18:38.034 --> 18:39.369
-[Jake] Come back!
-Great.

18:39.536 --> 18:41.704
Um, FYI,
tonight is pizza night.

18:41.871 --> 18:43.998
So is tomorrow and Wednesday.
Have a good day.

18:44.165 --> 18:45.208
Gaynor.

18:47.252 --> 18:49.879
I know that you think
you have this all figured out,

18:50.046 --> 18:51.923
but you're too young
to raise a family.

18:52.090 --> 18:54.634
You're only 16.

18:54.801 --> 18:56.594
Turned 17 three weeks ago.

18:57.929 --> 18:59.264
Happy birthday.

19:02.141 --> 19:04.060
I bet your father
didn't remember either!

19:04.227 --> 19:05.061
[Terry] Huh?

19:05.228 --> 19:06.646
Nothing, sweetheart.

19:06.813 --> 19:09.732
[exhales deeply]
Be better, Pat.

19:09.899 --> 19:11.860
♪ ♪

19:12.026 --> 19:14.529
[tires squealing,
car horn honking]

19:14.696 --> 19:17.073
♪ ♪

19:17.240 --> 19:18.157
Wow.

19:18.324 --> 19:20.285
Where did Button
learn to drive?

19:20.451 --> 19:21.578
-TikTok. Jake, wait.
-Oh.

19:21.744 --> 19:23.413
Okay, remember,
you come straight home

19:23.580 --> 19:24.664
from school, all right?

19:24.831 --> 19:26.165
I can't.
I have basketball rehearsal.

19:26.291 --> 19:27.542
[Gaynor]
It's called practice, buddy.

19:27.709 --> 19:29.252
Jake.

19:29.419 --> 19:30.670
I love you.

19:32.422 --> 19:34.090
Hey, where do you think
you're going?

19:34.215 --> 19:36.009
Uh, I'm gonna pick
some things up.

19:36.134 --> 19:38.261
I made a shopping list.

19:38.428 --> 19:40.471
Jesus. Okay, just please
stay in the car.

19:40.638 --> 19:42.390
It's too dangerous.

19:42.515 --> 19:45.310
-I got to go to work.
-Well, that's not fair.

19:46.185 --> 19:49.314
No, I-I-I don't want to stay
in the car.

19:49.480 --> 19:50.398
I said no.

19:50.565 --> 19:53.318
♪ ♪

19:54.402 --> 19:55.445
Stay.

20:00.909 --> 20:02.702
I can be safe.

20:11.794 --> 20:14.255
[grunts]

20:22.180 --> 20:24.807
[screams]

20:24.974 --> 20:27.977
Holy fuckity!

20:28.144 --> 20:30.146
-[person] Are you okay, boss?
-[breathing heavily]

20:30.313 --> 20:32.815
Yeah, yeah. [chuckles]

20:32.982 --> 20:34.776
I think that shook
something loose.

20:34.943 --> 20:37.236
All right,
be careful there, chief.

20:37.403 --> 20:39.822
Name's not chief.

20:39.989 --> 20:41.824
My name's...

20:41.991 --> 20:43.326
Terry Phelps.

20:47.080 --> 20:50.750
I'm gonna get me
some "kigarettes"

20:50.875 --> 20:52.961
and sun dry.

20:54.128 --> 20:56.005
Ooh.

20:56.172 --> 20:57.423
Could you get that?

21:05.765 --> 21:08.518
[dog barking]

21:08.685 --> 21:10.645
[light music plays]

21:10.812 --> 21:12.480
I know. I know.

21:12.647 --> 21:14.190
I missed you the most, too.

21:14.357 --> 21:16.359
Shh, shh, shh.

21:16.526 --> 21:19.362
[music turns eerie]

21:19.529 --> 21:20.571
[dog barks]

21:20.738 --> 21:23.324
♪ ♪

21:25.994 --> 21:28.121
[dog barks]

21:28.287 --> 21:31.290
♪ ♪♪♪

21:32.458 --> 21:35.044
[muffled barking]

21:35.211 --> 21:38.214
♪ ♪♪♪

21:40.967 --> 21:43.845
[barking continues]

21:44.012 --> 21:45.972
♪ ♪

21:46.139 --> 21:48.391
-Ew.
-[dog barks]

21:49.559 --> 21:52.145
[gasps]

21:52.311 --> 21:55.648
[house groaning,
objects clattering]

21:55.815 --> 21:58.735
[ominous music plays]

21:58.860 --> 22:01.070
♪ ♪

22:01.237 --> 22:03.114
I am in control.

22:03.281 --> 22:06.242
♪ ♪

22:13.082 --> 22:15.918
[clattering continues]

22:16.085 --> 22:19.047
♪ ♪

22:22.383 --> 22:25.219
[steps creaking,
clattering continues]

22:25.386 --> 22:28.431
♪ ♪

22:31.684 --> 22:35.730
[creaking]

22:35.897 --> 22:38.816
♪ ♪

22:41.152 --> 22:43.196
I am in control.

22:43.362 --> 22:46.282
I am in...

22:47.867 --> 22:49.285
...control.

22:58.086 --> 23:01.089
♪ ♪

23:54.058 --> 23:55.017
[screams]

23:55.143 --> 23:57.687
[house groaning, clattering]

23:57.854 --> 23:59.480
It's just an old house.
It's just an old house.

23:59.605 --> 24:02.567
♪ ♪♪♪

24:04.068 --> 24:06.112
[both scream]

24:08.197 --> 24:12.577
Hey, sorry, Dad.
It was a total shit show today.

24:12.743 --> 24:15.288
-How are you?
-I'm great.

24:20.418 --> 24:22.503
Apparently I'm a smoker.

24:25.798 --> 24:28.509
[Pat] Uh, so are you here
as my friend or my editor?

24:28.676 --> 24:30.636
Don't be so cynical.
I'm here as your editor.

24:30.803 --> 24:33.389
Your friend would know
that you hate flowers.

24:33.556 --> 24:34.765
I'd like to talk
about the book.

24:34.932 --> 24:36.100
[Pat] Oh, yes.

24:36.267 --> 24:38.394
I've been dying
to get back to work on it.

24:38.561 --> 24:40.605
I think
that we switch the focus

24:40.771 --> 24:42.356
from Rosemary to Cressida.

24:42.481 --> 24:44.066
We have her get committed.

24:44.233 --> 24:47.028
I have such amazing
asylum stories, Kam.

24:47.195 --> 24:49.280
-[chuckles] I'll bet.
-Yeah, she goes through hell.

24:49.447 --> 24:51.741
She comes out the other side
even stronger.

24:51.908 --> 24:54.035
I think this could be
a really important book

24:54.202 --> 24:56.329
about women's mental health.

24:56.495 --> 24:58.080
We call it Cressida Recovered.

24:58.247 --> 25:00.041
Oh, I fucking love it.

25:00.208 --> 25:02.418
Let's put a pin in that,
and I'm gonna show you

25:02.585 --> 25:04.587
what the marketing team
came up with.

25:07.506 --> 25:09.091
Wait. You already published it?

25:09.258 --> 25:11.219
No. I mean, technically, yes,

25:11.344 --> 25:14.013
but it doesn't hit the shelves
for another couple weeks.

25:14.180 --> 25:16.891
[sighs] You can't do this
without my permission.

25:17.058 --> 25:19.268
You're a writer.
We can do whatever we want.

25:19.435 --> 25:22.104
We paid you,
plus it's really good.

25:22.230 --> 25:25.399
-It's just a pulpy slasher.
-I disagree.

25:25.524 --> 25:27.026
I think it's everything
that you've been talking about.

25:27.193 --> 25:28.861
[chuckles] The last 16 pages

25:29.028 --> 25:31.822
is Rosemary chopping up
her family with an axe.

25:31.989 --> 25:33.491
Where is the recovery?

25:33.658 --> 25:35.660
You are the recovery.

25:35.785 --> 25:37.828
That's what you'll talk about
on the book tour.

25:37.995 --> 25:40.998
How this book helped you
with your healing process.

25:41.123 --> 25:42.541
[Pat] There's a tour?

25:42.708 --> 25:45.461
Yeah, I don't want to be
some mental patient on display.

25:45.628 --> 25:47.505
Nobody wants that either.

25:47.672 --> 25:49.340
Really? Is this a typo?

25:49.507 --> 25:50.883
[Kam] You're looking
at the straitjacket.

25:51.008 --> 25:53.928
I am looking at how incredible
your skin looks.

25:54.095 --> 25:55.805
Okay, look, we will regroup,

25:55.972 --> 25:57.473
come up
with a new marketing strategy,

25:57.640 --> 25:59.016
which, if we go
with the deranged thing,

25:59.183 --> 26:00.810
you're gonna have to keep
your hair like that.

26:00.977 --> 26:03.312
Oh, my gosh.
What am I supposed to do now?

26:03.479 --> 26:05.314
As your friend, take it easy.

26:05.481 --> 26:08.150
You're home.
Just enjoy your family.

26:08.317 --> 26:11.445
-Hmm.
-[knock on door]

26:11.570 --> 26:13.197
Mommy, I hate my family.

26:13.364 --> 26:15.741
I know. Me too.

26:15.908 --> 26:17.535
Come on in.

26:17.702 --> 26:20.997
Take off your shoes.
I just had the carpets cleaned.

26:21.163 --> 26:23.165
The kids don't want me,
Terry doesn't know me,

26:23.332 --> 26:24.750
and even Roxy is phoning it in.

26:24.917 --> 26:27.044
I just--nobody gives a hoot
that I'm home.

26:27.211 --> 26:29.171
[gasps]
They got rid of the cursing.

26:29.338 --> 26:31.799
Don't worry. That comes back
in a big fucking way.

26:31.966 --> 26:33.926
Come on,
I'll get you some seltzer.

26:34.051 --> 26:36.679
-[sighs]
-Oh, that's new.

26:36.846 --> 26:38.431
[Joan] Oh, yeah, Tommy left me.

26:38.556 --> 26:41.267
So I took the money
and bought baby sharks.

26:41.392 --> 26:42.727
Isn't it fun?

26:42.893 --> 26:44.520
You should see
what they do to a chicken.

26:44.687 --> 26:48.024
-I didn't know Tommy had money.
-Tommy was a bum.

26:48.149 --> 26:50.735
-I took the advance money.
-From my book?

26:50.901 --> 26:52.653
That--that's supposed to be
for the kids.

26:52.820 --> 26:54.739
The kids are fine.

26:54.905 --> 26:57.199
And it's practically my book.

26:57.325 --> 26:59.785
A beautiful,
sexually active housewife--

26:59.952 --> 27:01.537
you're lucky I don't sue you.

27:01.704 --> 27:03.372
Why is everything so terrible?

27:03.539 --> 27:04.957
What'd you think
would happen, darling?

27:05.124 --> 27:07.293
You'd go away,
get your brains scrabbled,

27:07.460 --> 27:09.920
come back better,
and life would be perfect?

27:10.046 --> 27:12.631
Yeah, that's exactly
what I thought would happen.

27:12.798 --> 27:15.343
Once I was cured,
everything would be better.

27:15.468 --> 27:18.554
No, no, honey, there's
no such thing as cured.

27:18.721 --> 27:20.973
You can't ever get rid
of mental illness.

27:21.140 --> 27:23.642
That shit is like glitter.

27:23.809 --> 27:26.312
So I'm back to where I started.

27:26.479 --> 27:29.440
-You--you hear voices?
-No.

27:29.607 --> 27:31.317
-You want to end your own life?
-No.

27:31.484 --> 27:34.362
-The ghost come back?
-No.

27:36.822 --> 27:39.700
Then you're miles
from where you started.

27:39.867 --> 27:41.494
Come on.

27:41.660 --> 27:44.455
Let's go watch the sharks.
It'll relax you.

27:44.622 --> 27:46.082
[Pat]
I just thought I'd be missed.

27:46.207 --> 27:47.792
Oh, you'd have to disappear

27:47.958 --> 27:51.087
for a lot longer
than four months.

27:51.253 --> 27:53.422
And you can't run away
from your family.

27:53.589 --> 27:54.924
You did.

27:55.049 --> 27:57.218
No--and now I have to have
this fucking conversation.

27:57.385 --> 27:59.053
-[scoffs]
-Cheers.

27:59.220 --> 28:00.262
[glasses clink]

28:01.430 --> 28:02.807
Can I stay here
for a little while?

28:02.973 --> 28:05.267
No, you cannot. You go home.

28:05.434 --> 28:08.020
You go fight for your husband.
Fight for your family.

28:10.815 --> 28:12.316
Fight the urge to do something

28:12.441 --> 28:15.444
that sends you back
to that hospital.

28:15.611 --> 28:19.115
And if all else fails,
get yourself some sharks.

28:19.281 --> 28:22.118
[light music playing]

28:22.284 --> 28:24.412
♪ ♪♪♪

28:24.537 --> 28:27.206
Welcome home.
I made meatloaf surprise.

28:27.373 --> 28:28.958
Oh, here we fucking go again.

28:29.083 --> 28:30.459
[Jake] You better
not be messing with me.

28:30.584 --> 28:32.128
Meatloaf surprise
is my favorite.

28:32.294 --> 28:33.754
Remember when I found
a Jolly Rancher?

28:33.921 --> 28:36.048
It really turned
my fifth-grade year around.

28:36.173 --> 28:38.384
I'm not messing with you.
Where's your dad?

28:38.551 --> 28:40.261
Oh, he wanted to get
out of the car by himself,

28:40.386 --> 28:41.971
-so don't wait up.
-I'll go help him.

28:42.138 --> 28:43.681
No, he doesn't need your help.

28:43.848 --> 28:45.933
Meatloaf surprise is supposed
to have surprises in it.

28:46.100 --> 28:49.687
-This is just meat and loaf.
-Keep looking.

28:49.854 --> 28:51.689
Okay, I'm gonna go eat
in my room.

28:51.856 --> 28:54.567
Gaynor, come on. I'm sorry.

28:54.733 --> 28:56.360
I'm sorry for all of this.

28:56.527 --> 28:58.279
I really do know
exactly what you're feeling.

28:58.446 --> 29:00.322
I really don't think
you do, Mom.

29:02.116 --> 29:03.242
Wait.

29:04.493 --> 29:05.870
[Gaynor grunts softly]

29:05.995 --> 29:08.664
When I was your age,
I had my mother committed.

29:08.831 --> 29:11.750
I gave up college
to take care of her.

29:11.917 --> 29:14.336
It took me a long time
to forgive her.

29:14.503 --> 29:16.505
I was just waiting
for the right time to tell you.

29:16.672 --> 29:17.715
Grandma told me last year.

29:17.882 --> 29:19.175
I hate her so much.

29:19.341 --> 29:22.761
Yeah, I guess
we both have bad moms, then.

29:22.928 --> 29:24.346
Mm-hmm, we do,

29:24.513 --> 29:26.599
but I'm not leaving.

29:26.724 --> 29:28.392
And I will make this up to you.

29:28.559 --> 29:30.603
Nobody wants you here.

29:30.728 --> 29:33.355
You broke this family.

29:33.522 --> 29:36.525
An onion? Is that the surprise?

29:36.692 --> 29:37.860
I am so mad right now.

29:38.027 --> 29:39.528
Eat pizza, then. I don't care.

29:39.695 --> 29:42.990
-Don't yell at my brother!
-I'm not yelling!

29:43.115 --> 29:45.910
I just--I just want this
to go back to a normal,

29:46.076 --> 29:47.369
gosh darn family!

29:47.495 --> 29:49.622
Stop saying normal,
'cause we're not normal!

29:49.788 --> 29:51.290
We have never been normal!

29:51.457 --> 29:52.458
[Terry] Button's right.

29:52.625 --> 29:55.461
[dramatic rock music plays]

29:55.628 --> 29:57.379
♪ ♪

29:57.546 --> 30:00.257
These last few days...

30:00.424 --> 30:01.800
I've...

30:01.967 --> 30:04.637
gotten to meet every one of you
all over again,

30:04.803 --> 30:06.680
and she's right.

30:06.847 --> 30:09.725
You aren't normal.
None of you are.

30:11.685 --> 30:14.897
What you are is amazing.

30:15.064 --> 30:17.983
We are amazing.

30:18.150 --> 30:20.027
Are you smoking?

30:20.194 --> 30:21.987
We are smokers.

30:22.154 --> 30:24.532
[chuckles] No, we are not.

30:25.866 --> 30:27.701
But we are a family.

30:27.868 --> 30:31.330
That's right, honey. We are.
We--we are...

30:32.581 --> 30:34.458
We...

30:34.583 --> 30:35.960
we are...

30:36.126 --> 30:38.671
♪ ♪♪♪

30:38.837 --> 30:41.048
Come on, Dad.

30:41.215 --> 30:44.176
♪ ♪

30:45.302 --> 30:46.762
...Phelps.

30:46.929 --> 30:49.557
Yes. We are Phelps.

30:49.723 --> 30:52.476
♪ ♪

30:52.643 --> 30:54.562
We are Phelps.

30:54.728 --> 30:57.606
-[Pat] We...
-[both] ...are Phelps.

30:57.773 --> 31:00.776
We are Phelps.

31:00.943 --> 31:02.027
We are Phelps!

31:02.194 --> 31:03.153
That's right!

31:03.320 --> 31:05.364
[Terry and Jake] We are Phelps!

31:05.489 --> 31:09.034
[all chanting] We are Phelps!
We are Phelps!

31:09.201 --> 31:10.911
I remember. Come on, Button.

31:11.036 --> 31:12.746
[all] We are Phelps!

31:12.913 --> 31:14.790
-We are Phelps!
-[barks]

31:14.915 --> 31:16.542
-We are Phelps!
-He is Phelps!

31:16.709 --> 31:18.627
-[static whirring]
-[all] We are Phelps!

31:18.752 --> 31:20.045
We are Phelps!

31:20.212 --> 31:23.465
[muffled] We are Phelps!
We are Phelps!

31:23.632 --> 31:27.011
We are Phelps! We are Phelps!

31:27.177 --> 31:30.931
We are Phelps! We are Phelps!

31:31.098 --> 31:33.183
-We are Phelps!
-[doorbell rings]

31:33.309 --> 31:36.228
We are Phelps! We are Phelps!

31:36.395 --> 31:38.272
We are Phelps!

31:39.732 --> 31:42.776
Hello, dear.
So good to see you.

31:42.943 --> 31:45.779
♪ ♪

31:45.904 --> 31:46.989
Fuck.

31:48.365 --> 31:50.701
[singer] ♪ La, la, la, la ♪

